Didn't you say you're taking
the college entrance exam this year?

794
00:51:10,440 --> 00:51:12,320
-Aren't you underage?
-This is my fifth retake.

795
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:13,800
I'm probably older than you.

796
00:51:16,120 --> 00:51:18,840
What are you going to do?
Are you going to settle the case?

797
00:51:20,360 --> 00:51:24,040
Mr. Hwang. Hey, Byung-sim,
don't settle the case.

798
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:26,280
A girl like her needs to learn her lesson.

799
00:51:26,360 --> 00:51:28,120
-People keep settling the case
-Listen to her.

800
00:51:28,200 --> 00:51:30,480
and she keeps making more victims
like you.

801
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:39,440
How dare you cry?

802
00:51:39,640 --> 00:51:41,040
Hey, stop crying.

803
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:43,080
Did Freud tell you
to cry in times like these?

804
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:52,640
May I leave?

805
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:56,200
Do I have to wait here
until he stops crying?

806
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:54,640
(Mi-ran.)

807
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:57,240
(This is Director Ma Dong-chan.)

808
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,080
(Can we meet?)

809
00:53:09,280 --> 00:53:10,320
Here.

810
00:53:15,640 --> 00:53:18,520
Hyun-gi told me that you like this drink.

811
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:21,280
This is the only drink that
the broadcasting company gives out.

812
00:53:21,720 --> 00:53:23,360
I only drank it
because they gave it to me.

813
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,920
I really like free stuff.

814
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:27,400
Just for your information,

815
00:53:28,120 --> 00:53:29,720
I hate this drink.

816
00:53:33,560 --> 00:53:35,200
Oh, I see.

817
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:36,920
Anyway,

818
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:39,680
I should've gotten to know you better.

819
00:53:39,760 --> 00:53:41,320
I'm sorry for doing it now.

820
00:53:43,600 --> 00:53:44,640
Mi-ran.

821
00:53:46,600 --> 00:53:47,720
What's your dream?

822
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:51,320
My dream is to earn a living.

823
00:53:51,840 --> 00:53:54,840
It's to make decent money
and live a happy life.

824
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:00,120
You and I really do think alike.

825
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:02,560
Director Ma.

826
00:54:02,960 --> 00:54:04,040
You're trying to convince me

827
00:54:04,120 --> 00:54:05,720
to participate in the experiment,
aren't you?

828
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:08,320
Do you know how pretentious you look?

829
00:54:08,400 --> 00:54:10,480
I can see you're having a hard time
putting on a fake smile.

830
00:54:11,400 --> 00:54:12,480
Yes, you're right.

831
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:14,880
I came to convince you.

832
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:16,040
But

833
00:54:17,560 --> 00:54:20,480
this smile isn't fake.
I can't put on a fake smile.

834
00:54:24,120 --> 00:54:25,120
Mi-ran.

835
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:30,200
You don't need to do it
if you don't feel like it.

836
00:54:38,040 --> 00:54:39,800
I went to the park to convince you,

837
00:54:39,880 --> 00:54:42,320
and that's where I saw you
beat up your boyfriend.

838
00:54:44,400 --> 00:54:45,440
You did a great job.

839
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:47,520
It was an impressive way to take revenge

840
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:48,960
on your cheating boyfriend.

841
00:54:50,200 --> 00:54:52,880
I saw the anger
and your spirit of challenge

842
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:54,520
that lies deep in your heart.

843
00:54:54,640 --> 00:54:57,560
It was so impressive that I actually
dreamt of you that night.

844
00:54:57,640 --> 00:55:00,280
I guess you get impressed
by really weird things.

845
00:55:00,360 --> 00:55:02,560
Or maybe you're a pervert.

846
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:06,120
Do you want to get abused
by someone or something?

847
00:55:08,120 --> 00:55:09,160
I've lived my life

848
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:12,840
doing things that other people don't do.

849
00:55:13,160 --> 00:55:15,720
And whenever I see someone similar,
my brain releases dopamine.

850
00:55:16,640 --> 00:55:18,920
That's why I got interested
in the cryonics experiment.

851
00:55:20,760 --> 00:55:22,360
I started to think

852
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:25,560
that we could cure people
who have incurable illnesses

853
00:55:25,720 --> 00:55:27,640
if this experiment succeeds.

854
00:55:31,720 --> 00:55:33,520
We can't cure them now,

855
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:36,640
but they might be able to
get cured in the future.

856
00:55:40,360 --> 00:55:41,640
Isn't it incredible

857
00:55:42,240 --> 00:55:44,480
that you can actually take part

858
00:55:46,080 --> 00:55:47,400
in such a historical event?

859
00:55:49,840 --> 00:55:50,840
Do you really think

860
00:55:51,920 --> 00:55:53,360
they can get cured?

861
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:08,880
Just a second.

862
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:21,160
Nam-tae!

863
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:22,960
Nam-tae!

864
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:25,160
Nam-tae, where are you?

865
00:56:25,840 --> 00:56:27,960
Nam-tae! Nam-tae!

866
00:56:28,320 --> 00:56:29,360
Nam-tae!

867
00:56:30,080 --> 00:56:32,480
Nam-tae! Nam-tae!

868
00:56:33,400 --> 00:56:34,440
Nam-tae!

869
00:56:37,640 --> 00:56:39,960
-Nam-tae!
-Mi-ran.

870
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:47,520
What are you doing here?
Do you know how worried I was?

871
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:55,000
Nam-tae.

872
00:56:55,920 --> 00:56:58,120
If your bag got tied to the pole,

873
00:56:58,760 --> 00:57:01,480
you could've just left the bag here
and come home.

874
00:57:34,960 --> 00:57:35,960
Hey.

875
00:57:37,400 --> 00:57:38,440
Mi-ran.

876
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:43,000
You don't need to do it
if you don't want to.

877
00:57:43,440 --> 00:57:44,600
I'll just do it by myself.

878
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:46,520
I need to get going.

879
00:57:56,320 --> 00:57:59,280
(I'll do it. I'll participate
in the experiment.)

880
00:57:59,800 --> 00:58:02,480
(-I'm going to do it by myself.
-Why won't you let me do it?)

881
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:05,560
(Ask your parents for permission.
If they say no, you can't do it.)

882
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:08,920
I'm not a kid.

883
00:58:09,240 --> 00:58:11,640
And what kind of parent
would let their child do that?

884
00:58:12,360 --> 00:58:14,960
I'm going to do it no matter what,
so just keep that in mind.

885
00:58:16,640 --> 00:58:18,960
But on one condition.

886
00:58:19,680 --> 00:58:20,720
What's that?

887
00:58:21,040 --> 00:58:23,680
Can I get autographs
from all the Fin.K.L members?

888
00:58:24,080 --> 00:58:25,520
My little brother's a huge fan.

889
00:58:26,080 --> 00:58:29,000
And I heard Leslie Cheung
will be visiting Korea next month.

890
00:58:29,320 --> 00:58:31,680
Can you let me meet him?

891
00:58:34,400 --> 00:58:36,400
(You know what's funny?)

892
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:41,240
Later on, Dong-chan wouldn't let her do it

893
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:43,120
while Mi-ran insisted on participating.

894
00:58:43,200 --> 00:58:45,400
-They fought again because of that.
-Really?

895
00:58:47,640 --> 00:58:49,400
They're both really crazy.

896
00:58:51,360 --> 00:58:53,640
They're going to wake up
after 2 hours and 30 minutes.

897
00:58:54,080 --> 00:58:55,240
I wonder how they would feel.

898
00:58:55,600 --> 00:58:57,920
Dong-chan would want to go to
a sauna as soon as he gets out.

899
00:59:00,840 --> 00:59:03,000
-I want you to leave right now.
-What?

900
00:59:03,200 --> 00:59:05,440
You can't shoot anything from now on.

901
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:06,680
You need to leave.

902
00:59:06,760 --> 00:59:08,200
What are you talking about?

903
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:09,720
We only have 2 hours and 30 minutes left.

904
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,600
You can't shoot the thawing process.

905
00:59:12,080 --> 00:59:14,360
Come back after two hours.
You can shoot outside.

906
00:59:14,440 --> 00:59:15,600
Get out of here. Hurry.

907
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:23,560
He won't let you shoot?
Are you kidding me?

908
00:59:23,640 --> 00:59:27,600
I guess he doesn't want to leak
the thawing process.

909
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:28,800
Well...

910
00:59:29,320 --> 00:59:31,800
It'll be like leaking
confidential information.

911
00:59:32,040 --> 00:59:35,920
Hyun-gi, do you think
something went wrong?

912
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:39,480
My gosh, no way. You don't need to worry.

913
00:59:39,720 --> 00:59:42,240
That's the only part that
he won't let us shoot.

914
00:59:42,320 --> 00:59:44,680
Director Ma will come back no matter what.

915
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:47,840
You know how famous restaurant owners

916
00:59:47,920 --> 00:59:51,600
don't even share their secret recipe
with their daughters-in-law?

917
00:59:51,800 --> 00:59:53,240
It's kind of similar to that.

918
00:59:53,560 --> 00:59:54,640
Are you sure?

919
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:57,720
If this goes wrong,
we'll all lose our jobs.

920
00:59:57,800 --> 01:00:00,040
Yes, of course. Don't worry.

921
01:00:00,120 --> 01:00:02,280
Tell Director Ma to come see me
as soon as he wakes up.

922
01:00:02,360 --> 01:00:04,120
Okay, I'll do that.

923
01:00:07,680 --> 01:00:09,400
Professor Hwang, are you going somewhere?

924
01:00:09,720 --> 01:00:10,920
There's somewhere I need to go.

925
01:00:11,000 --> 01:00:13,080
But we need to thaw their bodies
in less than two hours.

926
01:00:13,160 --> 01:00:14,400
I'll be back before then.

927
01:00:15,040 --> 01:00:17,720
I want you to keep an eye on the capsules.

928
01:00:18,840 --> 01:00:20,120
Don't let anyone inside.

929
01:00:20,600 --> 01:00:21,600
Okay.

930
01:00:48,720 --> 01:00:51,800
"Everyone, our country just managed to
freeze a living human being "

931
01:00:51,880 --> 01:00:54,320
"for the first time in human history."

932
01:00:55,040 --> 01:00:56,200
"Can you believe that?"

933
01:00:56,920 --> 01:01:00,640
"It's the birth of cryonics
which is something we only saw "

934
01:01:02,240 --> 01:01:03,200
"in movies."

935
01:01:03,280 --> 01:01:04,240
(Everyone, our country just managed to
freeze a living human being )

936
01:01:04,320 --> 01:01:05,280
(for the first time in human history.)

937
01:01:05,360 --> 01:01:07,280
"But that actually came true
in real life."

938
01:01:10,440 --> 01:01:12,520
"How do you feel now that you're awake?"

939
01:01:13,120 --> 01:01:16,440
"What did you dream of
during your 24 hours of sleep?"

940
01:01:19,720 --> 01:01:22,080
(How do you feel now that you're awake?)

941
01:01:23,840 --> 01:01:27,560
(Were you ever worried that you might not
wake up?)

942
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:40,240
(Variety Team 1)

943
01:01:42,880 --> 01:01:44,640
(Ma Dong-chan)

944
01:01:44,720 --> 01:01:46,680
I dare you to come back.

945
01:01:47,280 --> 01:01:50,400
(Ma Dong-chan)

946
01:01:55,800 --> 01:01:57,200
(Renowned bio-research professor missing,
Russian mobs are related?)

947
01:02:02,280 --> 01:02:05,080
("5 years, Doctor Johnson gone missing,
Murder or Not")

948
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:07,320
What is all this?

949
01:04:19,000 --> 01:04:21,560
(Name: Ma Dong-chan)

950
01:04:34,760 --> 01:04:36,240
(Warning)

951
01:04:48,320 --> 01:04:50,720
What's going on? What's wrong?

952
01:05:03,560 --> 01:05:05,960
Excuse me. We're ready to film!

953
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:07,680
What's wrong?

954
01:05:07,760 --> 01:05:09,480
Are they okay in there?

955
01:06:52,320 --> 01:06:54,240
(Melting Me Softly)

956
01:06:54,320 --> 01:06:56,080
(He's still alive.)

957
01:06:56,160 --> 01:06:57,840
(Dong-chan's alive?)

958
01:06:57,920 --> 01:06:59,640
-2019.
(-You slept for 20 years)

959
01:06:59,720 --> 01:07:01,400
(in the cryonics capsule.)

960
01:07:01,480 --> 01:07:03,920
(-44?
-My family disappeared.)

961
01:07:04,000 --> 01:07:06,120
(When was the last time
you saw your family?)

962
01:07:06,200 --> 01:07:07,200
Yesterday.

963
01:07:07,720 --> 01:07:09,120
(The bus fare went up a long time ago.)

964
01:07:09,200 --> 01:07:12,520
Hello, everyone. You're watching Newsline,
and this is Na Ha-young.

965
01:07:12,600 --> 01:07:13,640
(You punk!)

966
01:07:13,720 --> 01:07:16,520
-What's the date today?
-Dong-chan!

967
01:07:16,600 --> 01:07:20,000
It's me. Hyun-gi.

968
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:21,120
(Do you know me?)
